@startuml 22-autonomic-cycle
title Autonomic Kernel Cycle — observe → infer → propose → accept → execute → adapt

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

interface "AutonomicKernel\n(src/autonomic/kernel.rs)" as AK {
  + observe(log: &EventLog) → Observation
  + infer(obs: &Observation) → Inference
  + propose(inf: &Inference) → Proposal
  + accept(p: &Proposal) → Decision
  + execute(d: &Decision) → Effect
  + adapt(effect: &Effect)
}

component "DefaultKernel\n(src/autonomic/kernel.rs)\nBaseline — no Vision 2030 guards" as DK

component "Vision2030Kernel\n(src/autonomic/vision_2030_kernel.rs)\nExtended — KPI guards, autonomic\npolicy from AutonomicConfig" as VK

component "AutonomicConfig\n(dteam.toml → src/config.rs)\n[autonomic] guards + policy\n[rl] learning_rate / discount / exploration" as CFG

component "EventLog\n(XES traces)" as EL
component "PetriNet\n(current discovered model)" as PN
component "RL Agent ensemble" as RLAGENT

AK <|.. DK
AK <|.. VK

CFG --> VK : policy + guard thresholds
CFG --> DK : rl hyperparams

EL --> AK : observe()
AK --> PN : propose() / execute() modifies net
AK --> RLAGENT : adapt() tunes RL hyperparams

note right of VK
  Vision2030Kernel adds KPI-aware guards:
  blocks proposals that violate configured
  autonomic policy thresholds before accept().
end note

note bottom of AK
  Cycle runs per-epoch (T3 ≤ 100µs).
  observe + infer are read-only.
  execute is the only write path.
  adapt feeds back into next epoch.
end note

@enduml
